---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import DocSidebar from '../../components/DocSidebar.astro';
import DocContent from '../../components/DocContent.astro';

const title = 'Deployment';
const currentPage = '/docs/deployment';

const content = `
<h2>Production Deployment</h2>
<p>Follow these steps to deploy VibePrint OS to a production kiosk machine.</p>

<h3>1. Prepare the environment</h3>
<pre><code>git clone https://github.com/momokii/thermavibe.git
cd thermavibe
cp .env.production .env</code></pre>
<p>Edit <code>.env</code> and fill in your production values. Values marked <code>[CHANGE ME]</code> must be set:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>APP_SECRET_KEY</code> — generate with <code>python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"</code></li>
  <li><code>ADMIN_PIN</code> — choose a secure PIN for admin dashboard access</li>
  <li><code>POSTGRES_PASSWORD</code> — choose a secure database password</li>
</ul>
<p>AI provider, payment, and hardware settings are configured via the admin panel after deployment.</p>

<h3>2. Deploy the stack</h3>
<pre><code>make prod</code></pre>
<p>This auto-detects connected cameras and printers, builds Docker images, runs database migrations, and starts all services.</p>

<h3>3. Verify the deployment</h3>
<pre><code># Check that all containers are running
docker compose ps

# Test the health endpoint
curl http://localhost:8000/health</code></pre>

<h3>4. Launch kiosk mode</h3>
<pre><code>bash scripts/start-kiosk.sh</code></pre>
<p>Opens Chromium in fullscreen kiosk mode pointing at the application. Override the URL:</p>
<pre><code>KIOSK_URL=http://192.168.1.100:8000 bash scripts/start-kiosk.sh</code></pre>

<h2>Systemd Auto-Start</h2>
<p>Install the included systemd service so VibePrint OS starts automatically on boot:</p>
<pre><code>sudo cp deploy/thermavibe.service /etc/systemd/system/
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable thermavibe
sudo systemctl start thermavibe</code></pre>
<p>Check status:</p>
<pre><code>sudo systemctl status thermavibe</code></pre>

<h2>Updates</h2>
<p>To update to the latest version:</p>
<pre><code>git pull
make prod</code></pre>

<h2>Backup</h2>
<p>The database stores all session data, analytics, and configuration. Back it up regularly:</p>
<pre><code>docker compose exec db pg_dump -U vibeprint vibeprint > backup.sql</code></pre>

<h2>Reverse Proxy (Optional)</h2>
<p>If you need HTTPS or want to serve on a custom domain, place a reverse proxy (nginx or Caddy) in front of the containers. In production mode, the backend serves both the API and the frontend SPA on port 8000.</p>
`;
---

<BaseLayout title="Deployment — VibePrint OS Docs">
  <div style="max-width: 72rem; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div class="doc-layout" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column;">
      <DocSidebar currentPage={currentPage} />
      <DocContent title={title} content={content} currentPage={currentPage} />
    </div>
  </div>
  <style>
  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .doc-layout { flex-direction: row !important; }
  }
</style>
</BaseLayout>
